quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  72,1,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "It has been revealed to me that a group (from three to ten in number) of jinn{1} listened (to this Qur’ân). They said: ‘Verily, we have heard a wonderful Recitation (this Qur’ân)!",footnotes:1:1
  72,2,"‘It guides to the Right Path, and we have believed therein, and we shall never join (in worship) anything with our Lord (Allâh)."
  72,3,"‘And He, exalted be the Majesty of our Lord, has taken neither a wife nor a son (or offspring or children).{1}",footnotes:1:1
  72,4,"‘And that the foolish among us [i.e. Iblîs (Satan) or the polytheists amongst the jinn] used to utter against Allâh that which was an enormity in falsehood."
  72,5,"‘And verily, we thought that men and jinn would not utter a lie against Allâh."
  72,6,"‘And verily, there were men among mankind who took shelter with the males among the jinn, but they (jinn) increased them (mankind) in sin and transgression."
  72,7,"‘And they thought as you thought, that Allâh will not send any Messenger (to mankind or jinn)."
  72,8,"‘And we have sought to reach the heaven; but found it filled with stern guards and flaming fires."
  72,9,"‘And verily, we used to sit there in stations, to (steal) a hearing, but any who listens now will find a flaming fire watching him in ambush."
  72,10,"‘And we know not whether evil is intended for those on earth, or whether their Lord intends for them a Right Path."